1
00:00:09,778 --> 00:00:10,211
Huh?

2
00:00:16,197 --> 00:00:16,770
Komachi!

3
00:00:18,912 --> 00:00:19,609
What?

4
00:00:20,222 --> 00:00:21,009
Uh...

5
00:00:23,310 --> 00:00:24,699
Can I get you coffee?

6
00:00:26,528 --> 00:00:27,256
Yeah.

7
00:00:28,859 --> 00:00:29,526
Okay.

8
00:00:39,921 --> 00:00:40,687
Here you go.

9
00:00:44,281 --> 00:00:45,797
Hold up... Komachi.

10
00:00:50,619 --> 00:00:51,737
Can I talk to you?

11
00:00:52,244 --> 00:00:53,959
Okay, I'll listen.

12
00:01:10,294 --> 00:01:12,698
However, don't you have something to say to me?

13
00:01:12,723 --> 00:01:13,104
Uh...

14
00:01:14,755 --> 00:01:15,915
Sorry about earlier.

15
00:01:16,173 --> 00:01:17,883
I shouldn't have said what I said to you.

16
00:01:17,925 --> 00:01:19,623
It wasn't just what you said to me.

17
00:01:19,729 --> 00:01:22,106
Your attitude and your personality were bad, as well.

18
00:01:22,191 --> 00:01:23,086
Your eyes too.

19
00:01:23,111 --> 00:01:23,899
That's true.

20
00:01:25,030 --> 00:01:27,869
At any rate, I'm sure there's
something else you did that was bad.

21
00:01:28,016 --> 00:01:29,295
Also, true.

22
00:01:29,502 --> 00:01:31,088
And you didn't apologize.

23
00:01:31,231 --> 00:01:32,479
Ah, you're right.

24
00:01:33,170 --> 00:01:35,460
But since it's you, Big Brother, it's okay.

25
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:37,244
And since I'm your little sister.

26
00:01:37,691 --> 00:01:38,611
I'll forgive you.

27
00:01:39,461 --> 00:01:43,111
Also... I'm really sorry for my behavior.

28
00:01:44,118 --> 00:01:45,555
What, don't worry about that.

29
00:01:45,739 --> 00:01:47,925
I forgive you. Because I'm your big bro.

30
00:01:47,950 --> 00:01:50,760
You really can be quite full of yourself, can't you Bro?

31
00:01:51,247 --> 00:01:52,926
So you gonna tell me what happened?

32
00:01:53,259 --> 00:01:54,459
It's a long story.

33
00:01:56,014 --> 00:01:56,978
That's okay.

34
00:03:28,538 --> 00:03:30,874
I swear... that's just like you.

35
00:03:31,498 --> 00:03:35,177
I mean, I do understand where you're
coming from because I'm your sister...

36
00:03:35,437 --> 00:03:38,523
And we've lived together for
basically forever, so I get it.

37
00:03:38,588 --> 00:03:41,695
I can say "wow, you are so dumb" then smile and move on.

38
00:03:42,009 --> 00:03:44,139
While thinking "He can't be helped" and that's it.

39
00:03:44,501 --> 00:03:46,978
Truthfully... I get a bit sad.

40
00:03:47,924 --> 00:03:49,504
But it's different for other people.

41
00:03:50,010 --> 00:03:52,719
They don't understand what you're
thinking and it can be hard on them.

42
00:03:53,369 --> 00:03:55,429
You're nice to me and treat me as an equal...

43
00:03:55,811 --> 00:03:59,048
but I think you're only capable of
that because I'm your little sister.

44
00:03:59,648 --> 00:04:01,672
And most likely, if I weren't your sister...

45
00:04:01,805 --> 00:04:04,264
you wouldn't talk to me or even come anywhere near me.

46
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,946
Well, aside from that point,

47
00:04:07,779 --> 00:04:10,027
I'm really lucky to have you as my sister, you know.

48
00:04:10,821 --> 00:04:12,724
I bet I got a lot of points from that line.

49
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:14,897
Uh! Wow Big Brother that's so...

50
00:04:19,131 --> 00:04:20,877
That's sweet but if you weren't my big brother,

51
00:04:20,902 --> 00:04:24,549
I absolutely wouldn't come near you and
would completely ignore you so there's that.

52
00:04:24,574 --> 00:04:28,306
Maybe so but I do have some good
points, wouldn't you agree Little Sister?

53
00:04:28,364 --> 00:04:30,901
Nope not at all. You're actually really annoying.

54
00:04:31,268 --> 00:04:31,810
Hm...

55
00:04:34,085 --> 00:04:35,438
But you know...

56
00:04:35,878 --> 00:04:40,562
If you are together with someone for 15 long
years, you can't really help but grow attached to them.

57
00:04:40,821 --> 00:04:43,342
Oh, I bet you I got a lot of points from that great line!

58
00:04:43,676 --> 00:04:46,082
Well, 15 years is a long time.

59
00:04:46,599 --> 00:04:48,003
And then another fifteen.

60
00:04:48,148 --> 00:04:52,014
Actually, more time will pass because
we have all the time in the world.

61
00:04:52,039 --> 00:04:53,079
Quit yammering.

62
00:04:53,421 --> 00:04:56,201
How many years do you think I've
been listening to you yammer on and on?

63
00:04:56,226 --> 00:04:58,316
And will keep listening for many more to come!

64
00:04:58,997 --> 00:04:59,668
Do you get it?

65
00:05:00,696 --> 00:05:01,717
Y-yeah...

66
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:04,605
It's not only you.

67
00:05:05,073 --> 00:05:06,977
I have a future I need to protect too.

68
00:05:07,401 --> 00:05:10,401
I really like Yukino and Yui a lot, they're super cool.

69
00:05:10,597 --> 00:05:13,476
So if you break up the club, I'm going to be upset.

70
00:05:14,127 --> 00:05:16,195
So please... just for my sake...

71
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:20,172
and for the sakes of my friends... can't you do something?

72
00:05:20,948 --> 00:05:23,042
Well if it's for you, I guess I'll have to.

73
00:05:23,357 --> 00:05:25,655
Mhm. Doing it for me is a great idea.

74
00:05:25,865 --> 00:05:27,956
But that's just because I'm so selfish...

75
00:05:27,981 --> 00:05:29,231
I really can't help it.

76
00:05:29,256 --> 00:05:30,444
That is so true.

77
00:05:32,658 --> 00:05:33,565
Thanks for the talk.

78
00:05:34,725 --> 00:05:36,064
You're welcome Big Brother.

79
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,326
<i>After all that...</i>

80
00:05:42,711 --> 00:05:44,499
<i>that's the answer Komachi gave me.</i>

81
00:05:45,499 --> 00:05:47,346
<i>I was searching for the reason somewhere...</i>

82
00:05:48,076 --> 00:05:51,286
<i>to protect that place... and the time we all spend there.</i>

83
00:05:52,309 --> 00:05:56,953
<i>To prevent Yukino Yukinoshita and Yui
Yuigahama from becoming student council president,</i>

84
00:05:57,396 --> 00:05:59,304
<i>what can Hachiman Hikigaya do?</i>

85
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:01,974
<i>Well,</i>

86
00:06:02,986 --> 00:06:05,244
<i>I have no idea and that sucks!!</i>

87
00:06:08,407 --> 00:06:10,929
I know, how about getting rid of our uniforms?

88
00:06:10,954 --> 00:06:11,789
That's great!

89
00:06:11,942 --> 00:06:14,724
It would also be good if there were no more bag checks.

90
00:06:14,996 --> 00:06:16,408
Those are really annoying.

91
00:06:16,478 --> 00:06:19,805
They always seem to find the sexy
manga I've borrowed from my friends...

92
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:20,855
That's just you...

93
00:06:21,775 --> 00:06:22,762
I'll write it down.

94
00:06:22,787 --> 00:06:24,256
Please do not write that down.

95
00:06:24,325 --> 00:06:27,384
More important than "no more checking
our bags," I want to eat lunch on the roof.

96
00:06:27,426 --> 00:06:28,860
Oh, that's a great idea!

97
00:06:30,847 --> 00:06:31,363
Ugh!

98
00:06:36,477 --> 00:06:39,183
Oh, so pitiful, Hachiman Hikigaya!

99
00:06:39,709 --> 00:06:41,316
Stop saying dumb things.

100
00:06:42,105 --> 00:06:43,884
This pitifulness is my default.

101
00:06:44,317 --> 00:06:45,251
Something you want?

102
00:06:45,566 --> 00:06:46,819
Foolish question!

103
00:06:46,937 --> 00:06:49,220
I'm always hunkered down here during the lunch hour.

104
00:06:49,487 --> 00:06:53,404
Anyways my eyes came upon your
sadness, so I came to give you attention.

105
00:06:55,045 --> 00:06:56,078
What's wrong with you?

106
00:06:56,232 --> 00:06:58,211
Don't worry it's really not all that important.

107
00:06:58,236 --> 00:06:59,464
Wanna talk about it?

108
00:06:59,489 --> 00:07:00,424
No, that's okay.

109
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:02,680
Nothing anyone else needs to care or worry about.

110
00:07:02,705 --> 00:07:04,272
Don't be an idiot.

111
00:07:04,704 --> 00:07:09,039
Tell me Hachiman, to what extent have you
painfully listened to my drivel over the years?

112
00:07:09,352 --> 00:07:12,332
I'll listen to your idle gossip, since it's you.

113
00:07:13,571 --> 00:07:15,950
You know I'll admit I think I'm pretty cool here...

114
00:07:16,107 --> 00:07:17,559
lending a hand to the weak.

115
00:07:17,590 --> 00:07:20,029
Only what you said before that last thing was cool.

116
00:07:20,276 --> 00:07:22,147
So... did you steal that line?

117
00:07:22,189 --> 00:07:24,214
Nope... they're all my gems.

118
00:07:24,239 --> 00:07:24,994
Idiot.

119
00:07:25,304 --> 00:07:27,771
You know you're not really saying anything cool right now.

120
00:07:29,024 --> 00:07:31,206
Zaimokuza, I have a favor to ask.

121
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:33,302
Uh... um..

122
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:36,133
So, now as for how we can go about doing this...

123
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:37,637
Oh! There you are.

124
00:07:38,226 --> 00:07:38,890
Whoa!

125
00:07:39,206 --> 00:07:40,980
Hey, what are you doing here?

126
00:07:41,005 --> 00:07:43,538
Since you're out here working really hard for me Bro...

127
00:07:43,578 --> 00:07:45,599
I thought I should be doing the same for you!

128
00:07:45,895 --> 00:07:46,932
Ta-da!

129
00:07:46,957 --> 00:07:49,240
I found people who'll gladly work with you Bro!

130
00:07:49,265 --> 00:07:51,131
I can't believe I'm helping out.

131
00:07:51,156 --> 00:07:52,691
And do it with a smile.

132
00:07:52,921 --> 00:07:56,018
Let's start the "Campaign to Retain Yukino and Yui"!

133
00:07:56,181 --> 00:07:57,267
Oh yeah!

134
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,153
Not that I really care...

135
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:04,598
But if Yukinoshita and Yuigahama don't end up
running, who's going to be president in the end?

136
00:08:04,845 --> 00:08:05,206
Uh...

137
00:08:05,238 --> 00:08:06,620
Come on now...

138
00:08:07,508 --> 00:08:11,571
Um... tell me why we have to prevent
those two from being elected again?

139
00:08:11,672 --> 00:08:16,115
Really... I'm thinking going to war with
those two could be a very big mistake on our part.

140
00:08:16,345 --> 00:08:18,100
Yes, that is very true but...

141
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:22,695
Big Brother I wanna keep the service club
operating and I must have Yukino and Yui in it.

142
00:08:23,022 --> 00:08:25,843
Honestly I don't care about the student council elections.

143
00:08:25,868 --> 00:08:27,016
Okay?

144
00:08:27,723 --> 00:08:29,311
Then what do I do about Isshiki?

145
00:08:29,784 --> 00:08:33,107
Well whoever this Isshiki person
may be, is she important to you?

146
00:08:33,216 --> 00:08:34,287
No, not at all.

147
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:35,926
Then, why are you worried about it?

148
00:08:36,006 --> 00:08:38,433
Because a request is still a request Komachi.

149
00:08:38,599 --> 00:08:40,684
So, what's more important to you, your job or me?

150
00:08:40,726 --> 00:08:42,465
That's dumb, you, of course.

151
00:08:42,490 --> 00:08:43,818
I've no desire to work.

152
00:08:43,902 --> 00:08:45,546
Process of elimination.

153
00:08:45,639 --> 00:08:47,665
Well I guess I don't have to be happy about it...

154
00:08:48,117 --> 00:08:49,073
But, okay.

155
00:08:49,353 --> 00:08:51,033
So what are you going to do about it?

156
00:08:52,927 --> 00:08:53,939
<i>Let's see.</i>

157
00:08:55,694 --> 00:08:59,198
<i>The thing I should give the utmost
priority to is Komachi's request:</i>

158
00:08:59,223 --> 00:09:01,699
<i>Keeping Yukinoshita and Yuigahama in the club.</i>

159
00:09:02,536 --> 00:09:05,367
<i>Supporting the other candidates
is a difficult situation...</i>

160
00:09:05,631 --> 00:09:07,537
<i>so the card left to me is...</i>

161
00:09:10,092 --> 00:09:12,182
I can go try negotiating with Isshiki.

162
00:09:13,161 --> 00:09:15,135
Not gonna happen, she's a girl.

163
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:16,176
Will she even understand you?

164
00:09:16,201 --> 00:09:19,513
If Iroha Isshiki is playing that particular character...

165
00:09:20,251 --> 00:09:22,552
I'm going to say I'll have an easy negotiation.

166
00:09:23,258 --> 00:09:26,778
In the end... Isshiki just
wants to protect her brand image.

167
00:09:27,332 --> 00:09:28,324
So because of that...

168
00:09:28,566 --> 00:09:32,850
she wants to avoid the high risk-low
return issue of a vote of no confidence.

169
00:09:32,914 --> 00:09:33,815
Which means...

170
00:09:34,849 --> 00:09:36,668
My first approach was a mistake.

171
00:09:38,472 --> 00:09:39,242
Kawasaki.

172
00:09:39,378 --> 00:09:39,992
Hm?

173
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:42,519
Who do you think would be a
good student council president?

174
00:09:42,926 --> 00:09:44,506
Can you come up with a list of names?

175
00:09:44,615 --> 00:09:45,162
Huh?

176
00:09:47,311 --> 00:09:49,573
I'm thinking you too, I guess?

177
00:09:49,686 --> 00:09:50,133
Huh?

178
00:09:51,588 --> 00:09:53,203
Ha, that's really funny.

179
00:09:53,269 --> 00:09:56,218
There's no way I'd be able to
get nominations from 30 people.

180
00:09:56,635 --> 00:09:58,817
I know that. I just wanted to say it.

181
00:09:59,144 --> 00:10:00,014
Big Bro...

182
00:10:00,549 --> 00:10:02,962
Talk to Yukino and Yui about this, okay?

183
00:10:03,448 --> 00:10:04,462
Promise me?

184
00:10:04,732 --> 00:10:08,481
Yeah, but when I go present the idea
to them, I need to sound persuasive.

185
00:10:08,751 --> 00:10:10,234
So first I need to prepare.

186
00:10:10,532 --> 00:10:14,652
I'm worried that bad things will happen since
you're the type to argue for the sake of arguing.

187
00:10:14,887 --> 00:10:16,047
It'll be okay.

188
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:20,511
<i>I've now got a reason, a
problem, and a solution established.</i>

189
00:10:21,574 --> 00:10:23,554
<i>I just need to put it into action.</i>

190
00:10:32,854 --> 00:10:36,167
Oh, I would like you to put LCD tablets in the art room.

191
00:10:36,192 --> 00:10:37,634
LCD tablets?

192
00:10:46,881 --> 00:10:49,121
<i>One-third of the whole student body, huh?</i>

193
00:10:52,695 --> 00:10:53,158
It is I.

194
00:10:53,196 --> 00:10:56,377
We've got enough numbers... I'm
going to move on to the next step now.

195
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:59,832
Uh... This is not really a good tactic.

196
00:10:59,857 --> 00:11:01,491
This is fraught with danger.

197
00:11:01,710 --> 00:11:02,605
Zaimokuza...

198
00:11:02,630 --> 00:11:04,302
Oh, don't misunderstand me.

199
00:11:04,327 --> 00:11:06,079
It is not you I'm worried about!

200
00:11:06,104 --> 00:11:08,849
You see, I also assume responsibility by assisting,

201
00:11:08,874 --> 00:11:11,743
and the anxiety that you will
blame me for everything is terrible.

202
00:11:11,768 --> 00:11:14,865
And believe me in that instance, I am
prepared to tell everyone everything!

203
00:11:14,890 --> 00:11:17,856
You really are such trash Zaimokuza. Never change.

204
00:11:18,273 --> 00:11:19,174
It's okay though.

205
00:11:19,573 --> 00:11:20,840
They can search all they want.

206
00:11:21,048 --> 00:11:23,321
The person behind these accounts doesn't exist.

207
00:11:23,809 --> 00:11:24,985
No one's going to get hurt.

208
00:11:26,015 --> 00:11:27,130
Just keep this in mind...

209
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:31,649
As long as you don't go and make a
problem a problem, it won't be seen as one.

210
00:11:33,214 --> 00:11:34,449
Can you get Isshiki for me?

211
00:11:37,039 --> 00:11:37,465
Ah!

212
00:11:38,459 --> 00:11:38,958
Oh...

213
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:41,017
<i>Sorry, it's only me.</i>

214
00:11:41,881 --> 00:11:45,072
Copying down all of this stuff
is really difficult you know!

215
00:11:47,437 --> 00:11:52,450
Oh, so by the way, was the girl you were
hanging out with the other day Hayama's girlfriend?

216
00:11:52,475 --> 00:11:53,423
I have no idea.

217
00:11:53,474 --> 00:11:56,838
Come on, surely it's okay if you tell me... isn't it?

218
00:11:56,981 --> 00:11:57,950
When this is over.

219
00:12:00,065 --> 00:12:03,431
Whatever I don't really think that
will be much of a problem for me.

220
00:12:03,456 --> 00:12:04,698
Don't you think so too?

221
00:12:04,844 --> 00:12:08,112
So anyway... speaking of him do you like...

222
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:10,083
what do you think about him?

223
00:12:12,136 --> 00:12:12,515
