224
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:14,159
Are you trying to hit on me right now?

225
00:12:14,184 --> 00:12:16,605
Sorry, it can't happen, I have a crush on someone else.

226
00:12:16,630 --> 00:12:17,636
No, that's not it.

227
00:12:18,047 --> 00:12:20,662
I was just simply asking you
what you thought about Hayama.

228
00:12:20,687 --> 00:12:21,075
Oh...

229
00:12:21,570 --> 00:12:24,025
Hm... let me think about it for a second.

230
00:12:24,063 --> 00:12:26,864
At first I thought he was so cute, and I wanted to ki...

231
00:12:27,431 --> 00:12:30,109
I wanted to hold hands with him, or something but...

232
00:12:30,690 --> 00:12:32,525
<i>You just almost said you wanted to "kiss" him?</i>

233
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:33,644
So anyways...

234
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,397
Is there really a point in doing all of this?

235
00:12:36,941 --> 00:12:38,438
It's not like there isn't one.

236
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:41,360
You know the way you said that just now was kinda vague...

237
00:12:41,483 --> 00:12:45,563
There's no way to win against Yukinoshita
or Yuigahama... no matter what you do.

238
00:12:47,073 --> 00:12:49,127
It's pointless in that way.

239
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,656
Well, not that I would really want to...

240
00:12:54,762 --> 00:12:59,141
but I think it would be super
scary if I actually won the election.

241
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:01,356
It's not like you're gonna really win this.

242
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:04,244
Yeah... well...

243
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:09,125
Besides, whoever those people who nominated you
were, they won't really vote for you, will they?

244
00:13:11,429 --> 00:13:13,700
Those people are probably laughing hard right now.

245
00:13:14,015 --> 00:13:16,867
And, when they see you lose the
election, they'll laugh even more about it.

246
00:13:19,456 --> 00:13:21,252
That would make you mad, wouldn't it?

247
00:13:22,336 --> 00:13:25,933
However... wouldn't you want to give
them a taste of their own medicine?

248
00:13:27,342 --> 00:13:29,468
I do... well... I could do it I know I can...

249
00:13:29,493 --> 00:13:30,255
You can.

250
00:13:32,469 --> 00:13:34,327
You've been writing for quite a while now.

251
00:13:34,529 --> 00:13:35,646
Do you know what that is?

252
00:13:35,671 --> 00:13:37,592
It's the list of nominators, right?

253
00:13:37,711 --> 00:13:39,225
That's right. However...

254
00:13:39,691 --> 00:13:42,168
This here is the list of people that nominated you.

255
00:13:42,292 --> 00:13:42,822
Uh...

256
00:13:44,639 --> 00:13:45,188
Huh?

257
00:13:45,894 --> 00:13:49,819
But I already have enough, how can I possible
have more than the amount required to run?

258
00:13:49,851 --> 00:13:52,403
The rule says that there must be
at least thirty people to run...

259
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,456
but it's okay if you gather more.

260
00:13:55,313 --> 00:13:58,106
Someone is running an Isshiki support account, online.

261
00:13:58,901 --> 00:14:01,288
If just one-third of the student body supports you...

262
00:14:01,336 --> 00:14:03,245
then you can easily go and win this election.

263
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:06,342
I don't get where this came from? That's not possible.

264
00:14:06,688 --> 00:14:09,685
And even if I were to win this
thing, I wouldn't be a good president.

265
00:14:10,314 --> 00:14:12,318
I don't have confidence in myself.

266
00:14:12,527 --> 00:14:14,383
Plus I already belong to a club.

267
00:14:14,623 --> 00:14:16,890
I agree it would be difficult to deal with both.

268
00:14:16,924 --> 00:14:18,738
But what you would gain would be huge.

269
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:20,251
What do you think it is?

270
00:14:20,457 --> 00:14:21,108
What?

271
00:14:21,223 --> 00:14:24,007
Well, experience or something like that.

272
00:14:24,393 --> 00:14:26,080
And maybe a good recommendation.

273
00:14:26,438 --> 00:14:29,448
So for the record here... you're acting like a teacher.

274
00:14:29,473 --> 00:14:30,175
That's wrong.

275
00:14:30,624 --> 00:14:32,605
The thing you gain is the chance to say...

276
00:14:33,299 --> 00:14:37,748
"Even though I'm a freshman and student council
president, I'm doing my best and showing up to practice!"

277
00:14:38,021 --> 00:14:38,554
See?

278
00:14:38,881 --> 00:14:39,674
Ew.

279
00:14:41,292 --> 00:14:43,844
And when you're a freshman,
and you mess up, you're forgiven.

280
00:14:44,066 --> 00:14:47,494
You also have the excuse of going to
practice when student council gets annoying.

281
00:14:47,991 --> 00:14:49,425
And the opposite is also true.

282
00:14:49,603 --> 00:14:52,517
Yea, but it's still gonna be really difficult for me.

283
00:14:52,542 --> 00:14:53,335
What do I do?

284
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,667
When those times happen, you can consult Hayama.

285
00:14:56,137 --> 00:14:56,578
Huh?

286
00:14:56,864 --> 00:14:58,217
It's okay to accept his help.

287
00:14:58,439 --> 00:15:02,699
Hey, maybe you can make him keep an eye out for
you and walk you home after practice sometimes.

288
00:15:07,149 --> 00:15:10,093
No way, how are you actually even this smart?

289
00:15:10,210 --> 00:15:11,032
I just am.

290
00:15:12,213 --> 00:15:12,676
Hm...

291
00:15:13,828 --> 00:15:17,130
If this many people are supporting
me, I guess I can't say no.

292
00:15:17,595 --> 00:15:20,908
You know I've gotta say... your
suggestion is quite attractive.

293
00:15:21,413 --> 00:15:22,359
Let me tell you...

294
00:15:22,461 --> 00:15:25,465
it really hurts me being laughed
at by the kids in my class.

295
00:15:27,862 --> 00:15:30,037
Okay, I'll work with you. Let's win this!

296
00:15:35,323 --> 00:15:36,553
Have you changed your minds yet?

297
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:39,808
No I haven't. This is the best strategy.

298
00:15:40,231 --> 00:15:41,791
Mine hasn't changed, either.

299
00:15:41,816 --> 00:15:43,968
It's not necessary for you to run, too.

300
00:15:44,084 --> 00:15:46,217
It is. And I don't wanna lose.

301
00:15:46,581 --> 00:15:48,227
Actually why are you running?

302
00:15:48,336 --> 00:15:51,465
Because, if you aren't here Yukinon, the club will end.

303
00:15:52,026 --> 00:15:53,211
I don't want that to happen.

304
00:15:53,638 --> 00:15:55,184
It's not going to come to that.

305
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:56,170
It will!

306
00:15:56,489 --> 00:15:59,032
The truth is, you don't have to run in the election.

307
00:15:59,474 --> 00:16:02,014
Not just you, Yuigahama, you too, Yukinoshita.

308
00:16:02,130 --> 00:16:04,049
What are you even talking about?

309
00:16:04,264 --> 00:16:06,603
I'm pretty sure we rejected your crazy plan.

310
00:16:06,628 --> 00:16:08,338
You did, but it's not that plan.

311
00:16:08,435 --> 00:16:08,904
Huh?

312
00:16:09,020 --> 00:16:10,335
I already gave up on that.

313
00:16:14,029 --> 00:16:15,918
Did you have something to do with this?

314
00:16:16,145 --> 00:16:17,407
An interested party...

315
00:16:17,797 --> 00:16:19,284
I don't really know who it was though.

316
00:16:19,827 --> 00:16:20,640
I see.

317
00:16:20,665 --> 00:16:22,301
An amazing number of people.

318
00:16:22,326 --> 00:16:25,522
Yeah, it's about about one-third of
the student body of the high school.

319
00:16:25,849 --> 00:16:27,542
<i>This number is the actual truth.</i>

320
00:16:28,169 --> 00:16:31,970
<i>Although, it was impossible to
gather this much support for Isshiki...</i>

321
00:16:32,562 --> 00:16:35,522
<i>In other words, there's just one big lie in the moon.</i>

322
00:16:36,275 --> 00:16:37,243
I got it, okay?

323
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:38,389
Later man.

324
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:38,850
Out!

325
00:16:41,356 --> 00:16:42,769
<i>This is nothing but junk.</i>

326
00:16:43,598 --> 00:16:45,511
<i>It was just a tool used to persuade them.</i>

327
00:16:46,157 --> 00:16:48,867
<i>So... I just need to get through this day,</i>

328
00:16:49,501 --> 00:16:51,314
<i>and then get rid of the support accounts.</i>

329
00:16:51,693 --> 00:16:52,921
<i>Erase all of it.</i>

330
00:16:54,088 --> 00:16:55,766
In order for Isshiki to be president...

331
00:16:56,212 --> 00:16:58,916
I cleared all the requirements
and the shackles holding her down.

332
00:16:58,996 --> 00:17:03,177
So, there's no need for you to run
for student council president anymore.

333
00:17:08,063 --> 00:17:09,679
So a support account, huh?

334
00:17:23,504 --> 00:17:24,348
Well I'm glad.

335
00:17:26,447 --> 00:17:27,644
So, this is settled, right?

336
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,395
So... I see...

337
00:17:36,675 --> 00:17:39,972
You're telling us there's no
reason we need to act anymore.

338
00:17:40,791 --> 00:17:42,265
Yeah, I guess you don't, huh.

339
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:43,481
Yes.

340
00:17:46,772 --> 00:17:49,378
I really thought you of all people would understand.

341
00:17:49,558 --> 00:17:50,015
Uh?

342
00:17:51,398 --> 00:17:51,910
Huh?

343
00:17:52,191 --> 00:17:53,855
I guess I'll go tell the teachers.

344
00:17:54,389 --> 00:17:55,960
Uh! We'll come.

345
00:17:56,196 --> 00:17:57,600
Just one of us is enough.

346
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:15,416
Um... Sorry about that.

347
00:18:15,665 --> 00:18:17,596
Huh? Why are you apologizing?

348
00:18:18,008 --> 00:18:20,360
Well, you really worked on this didn't you?

349
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:23,752
Like, your public pledge, and the speech, and stuff.

350
00:18:24,011 --> 00:18:26,180
Oh that... that doesn't really matter.

351
00:18:26,205 --> 00:18:28,455
I bet you did a lot too, didn't you, Hikki?

352
00:18:28,609 --> 00:18:31,299
Oh wow, your hair has grown all long and straggly.

353
00:18:31,324 --> 00:18:32,436
Here, let me fix it.

354
00:18:33,189 --> 00:18:34,576
It doesn't need fixing.

355
00:18:34,891 --> 00:18:35,709
There, there.

356
00:18:40,612 --> 00:18:42,440
I bet you did your best too, huh?

357
00:18:42,972 --> 00:18:43,943
Not really...

358
00:18:51,828 --> 00:18:53,419
This place is important to me.

359
00:18:54,951 --> 00:18:56,588
And you somehow protected it.

360
00:18:59,557 --> 00:19:00,045
Hey...

361
00:19:01,251 --> 00:19:04,685
I knew that I probably wouldn't
beat Yukinon for the presidency,

362
00:19:05,275 --> 00:19:09,983
but then I also worried that if I did win, then I
wouldn't be able to come to the club activities anymore.

363
00:19:11,132 --> 00:19:13,931
And I have you to thank for all of this.

364
00:19:14,151 --> 00:19:15,255
You're wrong about that.

365
00:19:17,812 --> 00:19:18,665
That's enough.

366
00:19:30,675 --> 00:19:32,045
You did your best, Hikki!

367
00:19:32,237 --> 00:19:33,158
What are you saying?

368
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:36,135
Hikki did his best, huh?

369
00:19:36,181 --> 00:19:38,215
Stop... I didn't really do anything.

370
00:19:38,982 --> 00:19:39,897
That's true.

371
00:19:40,130 --> 00:19:42,185
I mean nothing we can actually see, right?

372
00:19:42,411 --> 00:19:43,917
But then again I know you...

373
00:19:44,494 --> 00:19:46,579
I bet you did something you didn't want to do.

374
00:19:47,305 --> 00:19:49,100
Maybe you wanted to change your ways...

375
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:51,744
however it's not something you can easily do.

376
00:19:53,028 --> 00:19:54,975
And your guilty conscious lingers.

377
00:19:56,698 --> 00:19:58,371
I couldn't really do anything,

378
00:19:58,689 --> 00:20:01,395
but even so I wondered if this was the right thing to do.

379
00:20:02,052 --> 00:20:04,669
So, it will probably bother you more, Hikki.

380
00:20:06,124 --> 00:20:08,197
Now we can go back to how it was before.

381
00:20:08,873 --> 00:20:09,953
I don't know about that.

382
00:20:12,501 --> 00:20:15,010
I really thought you of all people would understand.

383
00:20:18,458 --> 00:20:21,246
This club is not really that difficult to deal with,

384
00:20:21,271 --> 00:20:22,923
and I understand how the
student council activities work...

385
00:20:22,955 --> 00:20:24,497
<i>There are people that can't act...</i>

386
00:20:25,472 --> 00:20:26,960
<i>if they are not given a problem...</i>

387
00:20:27,718 --> 00:20:29,126
<i>and they can't find a reason.</i>

388
00:20:31,286 --> 00:20:33,181
<i>The only thing that remained for me...</i>

389
00:20:33,982 --> 00:20:37,237
<i>was the suspicion, I had made a big mistake.</i>

390
00:20:37,979 --> 00:20:39,126
Do you start working today?

391
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:40,410
I sure do!

392
00:20:41,084 --> 00:20:44,430
You know, I kinda don't think it'll
go so well in the beginning, though.

393
00:20:44,883 --> 00:20:47,589
Next year my little sister will enter this school.

394
00:20:47,674 --> 00:20:48,221
Oh?

395
00:20:48,756 --> 00:20:50,961
Listen, you better try and do a good job.

396
00:20:52,848 --> 00:20:53,360
Ah!

397
00:20:53,642 --> 00:20:57,979
What? Are you trying to hit on me? You are
being too obvious! It's uncomfortable! Sorry!

398
00:20:58,230 --> 00:21:00,887
<i>Seems you had a different reason for rejecting me before.</i>

399
00:21:01,309 --> 00:21:02,215
Good luck to you then...

400
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:03,580
Oh, Hikigaya.

401
00:21:07,346 --> 00:21:08,253
I can grab that.

402
00:21:08,825 --> 00:21:10,846
Thanks! I had more things than I thought.

403
00:21:11,122 --> 00:21:11,633
Ugh!

404
00:21:16,998 --> 00:21:19,057
Seems like it's a different room, huh?

405
00:21:21,894 --> 00:21:24,529
Man, I was really gunning for her too.

406
00:21:24,647 --> 00:21:25,079
What?

407
00:21:25,332 --> 00:21:28,419
I had thought Yukinoshita would
become the student council president.

408
00:21:28,846 --> 00:21:31,336
And then Yuigahama would become the vice president.

409
00:21:31,541 --> 00:21:32,928
And you'd be general affairs!

410
00:21:32,953 --> 00:21:35,162
You gave me a minor position? Wow.

411
00:21:35,254 --> 00:21:38,056
And, when I've graduated, I would sometimes come back...

412
00:21:38,081 --> 00:21:40,156
just to hang with you guys during meetings...

413
00:21:40,181 --> 00:21:41,829
And then I'd get to say things like,

414
00:21:41,854 --> 00:21:44,954
"The cultural festival and the
sports festival were so much fun!"

415
00:21:45,087 --> 00:21:46,520
And you guys did that!

416
00:21:48,130 --> 00:21:50,546
You know... I've always dreamt of that.

417
00:21:53,469 --> 00:21:55,329
<i>I've been thinking about consequences.</i>

418
00:21:55,785 --> 00:21:58,799
<i>What if... And this is purely hypothetical...</i>

419
00:21:59,609 --> 00:22:02,884
<i>What if we could go back to the last
save point and make a different choice?</i>

420
00:22:03,509 --> 00:22:04,675
<i>What do you think would've happened?</i>

421
00:22:05,339 --> 00:22:06,610
<i>Would things have been different?</i>

422
00:22:08,117 --> 00:22:10,064
<i>The answer is no.</i>

423
00:23:41,879 --> 00:23:45,373
Okay, surely that's everything by now, right, Iroha?

424
00:23:45,398 --> 00:23:48,844
Tobe, the refrigerator needs to
move, it's supposed to go in the corner.

425
00:23:48,869 --> 00:23:50,629
And the heater goes next to the desk.

426
00:23:50,654 --> 00:23:53,102
Aww... You should've told me that before.

427
00:23:53,175 --> 00:23:56,115
Hey, Iroha, I've gotta head
out to my seasonal Christmas job!

428
00:23:56,140 --> 00:24:00,509
But I'm bored now, and I want to finish remodeling
the student council room as soon as possible.

429
00:24:00,534 --> 00:24:01,849
O-okay.

430
00:24:01,981 --> 00:24:03,274
But I need to get to work.

431
00:24:03,299 --> 00:24:05,410
I wish Hayato would hurry up and get here!

432
00:24:05,435 --> 00:24:06,523
Uh. Hayama?

433
00:24:06,548 --> 00:24:08,973
Okay, Tobe! You can go ahead and leave right now.

434
00:24:09,412 --> 00:24:10,580
O-okay.

